      <hedline>
        <hl1>Test-Tampering Charge to Be Investigated</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">AP</byline>
      <dateline>FAIRFIELD, Conn., July 12</dateline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Nicholas A. Cioffi, the former State Public Safety Commissioner, has been hired to oversee the investigation of alleged test tampering at the Stratfield School, a public elementary school where higher than usual numbers of answers were changed on two standardized tests.</p>
        <p>Mr. Cioffi said today that he expected to start work on the investigation over the weekend and hoped to complete the major part of it by the opening of school in September.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Nicholas A. Cioffi, the former State Public Safety Commissioner, has been hired to oversee the investigation of alleged test tampering at the Stratfield School, a public elementary school where higher than usual numbers of answers were changed on two standardized tests.</p>
        <p>Mr. Cioffi said today that he expected to start work on the investigation over the weekend and hoped to complete the major part of it by the opening of school in September.</p>
        <p>A former Superior Court judge, Mr. Cioffi became public safety commissioner  in 1991. He now does consulting and mediation work.</p>
      </block>
